From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 21:14:44 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ==== mtier damon_{strt,stop}() failure handling fix ====

samples/damon/mtier: handle damon_{start,stop}() failures

DAMON sample module mtier can cause memory leak and use-after-free due
to its wrong handling of failures from damon_start() and damon_stop(),
respectively.  Fix those.

Changes from RFC v1
- RFC v1: https://lore.kernel.org/20260609005443.2122-1-sj@kernel.org
- Add damon_stop() failure handling fix to the series.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_dooefjwp | 0
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_dooefjwp

diff --git a/hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_dooefjwp b/hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_dooefjwp
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000..e69de29bb2d1d
-- 
2.47.3

